name: Manaia Necklace
description:
This is a new addition to my large sterling silver necklaces I've been making. 

Meaning behind the Manaia Necklace: The connection of mind, body and spirit. The greeting of honour and respect....

The Manaia is an ancient mythical being. It is said to be the messenger between the earthly world of mortals and the domain of the spirit world. It is a holder of great spiritual energy and is a guardian against evil. 

Solid Sterling Silver
Size: 183mm x 65mm
Black braided polyester cord with an adjustable dragon toggle for length.

name: Noveau Necklace
description:
Details for this necklace:

Sterling silver
Size: 163mm x 35mm x 2mm


Noveau Necklace:
The spiral (or curl) represents the opening of new life and purity to the world. It also represents peace, tranquillity and spirituality along with a strong sense of regrowth or a new beginning. It is also often associated with nurturing so when interlocked with others is frequently used to represent strength and purity, a maze creating a spiritual centre of vital energies. The pattern is symbolic of lifeâ€™s journey, and innovation of self-discovery through the maze of existence. This design in particular shows the joining together of two in unity. Even though they sometimes move away from each other on their own journey, they will always come together again sharing their lives and blending to become one. It tells how the strength of bond of friendship, loyalty and love will last forever.

name: Circle Pendant
description:
New circle pendant with a fusion of 3 materials: sterling silver, garnet cab stone and whale bone. Small pendant yet very eye catching, very elegant. 

Size of this pendant is 28mm round by 5mm deep.  

The closed circle is said to represent the circle of life which is, has no beginning or end. For an artist the circle represents the relationship or oneness between the artist and his or her craft, bringing together head, hand and heart.
